Secured and Monitored Web Infrastructure

Diagram
User -> DNS -> HAproxy -> Nginx Server 1 / Nginx Server 2 -> Application Server -> MySQL Primary/Replica
Each server has its own firewall and monitoring client.
HTTPS is terminated with an SSL certificate for www.foobar.com.

Why these elements are added
- Firewalls: restrict unwanted traffic and allow only required ports and services.
- SSL certificate: enables HTTPS and encrypts traffic between the user and the site.
- Monitoring clients: collect metrics and logs for a monitoring service such as Sumo Logic.

Why HTTPS
- HTTPS encrypts data in transit.
- It protects credentials, sessions, and user data from interception and tampering.

Monitoring
- Monitoring is used to track uptime, load, traffic, errors, and resource usage.
- The client on each server sends metrics to the monitoring service.
- To monitor web server QPS, collect request counts over time and compute queries per second from the access logs or server metrics.

Issues
- SSL termination at the load balancer creates a trust boundary issue because traffic is decrypted before reaching backend servers.
- Having only one MySQL server that accepts writes creates a bottleneck and a single point for write failures.
- Putting the same components on every server increases complexity and can make scaling and maintenance harder if one tier is overloaded.
